  "commit_subject": "[OCR] Extract pick_orientation(); fix annotation using wrong orientation code",
  "commit_body": "_annotate_image_b64 was calling correct_orientation() (variance only) while\nrecognize() uses the OCR-confidence tiebreaker for 90\u00b0/270\u00b0 ambiguity.  For\nIMG_4256 this caused the annotation to rotate to 90\u00b0 while OCR used 270\u00b0, so\nbboxes landed in the wrong position on the displayed image.\n\nFix: extract pick_orientation() from recognize() into a public function that\nincludes the tiebreaker, then use it in both recognize() and _annotate_image_b64.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
